Detailed Description

A class for encapsulating the methods for outputting values for a record from the Collector; but more optimized than CollectorOutputter. If an outputter implements this interface, startRecord, endRecord, and the various outputXxx methods won't be used. The intent is that an outputter object can choose to also support faster output; the connection handler may decide to use the fast outputter if it is supported.
